cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and speech recognition. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it involves audio recordings. Additionally, it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses machine learning techniques for classification. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as dialect identification is relevant in social and cultural contexts.
